name: Wiley S
text: Great airport. Stop in Sam's country kitchen for a all u can eat lunch.

name: Skiddster
text: Very friendly staff at the FBO and Sam's right next door for some great country cooking. However, it is Weedon Field and not Woodon Field.

name: Garrett Munguia
text: Really nice people. Self service fuel, newly painted ramp lines.

name: Kim Davenport
text: Neat little airport, well kept. Would love for them to replace weather station that was destroyed by last year's tornado. Even the weatherman for WSFA has begged for it so he can better determine our upcoming weather better!

name: D Rock
text:
Great airport.

Can someone remove the Chinese name from this airport in Google?

name: Allan Gassett
text: The only time I have been is for the Sunday buffet and it is absolutely great

name: Mike Marra
text:
Airport was destroyed by a massive tornado the first week of March 2019.

Best wishes on the rebuilding of this outstanding airport.

We also wish the aircraft owners all the best as they try to replace ALL the planes destroyed by the storm.

name: Jo Vaughn
text: We fly dogs out from here a lot

name: Joy Usry
text: Don't remember going there. Refresh my memory please!

name: Christopher Cannon
text: Went to KEUF in April 2017 and it was a fantastic experience! Eric was incredibly friendly and welcoming. The FBO itself is very clean and the fuel prices as low as you could expect. Will definitely be back when flying in the area.

name: Sue Ulrey
text: Friendly, efficient staff plus Sam's Restaurant next door make this a great stop!
